[49m[38;5;10m+       1[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Recipe 14.7: Python Implementation Example
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simplified, illustrative implementation of the OR case sequencing optimization from Recipe 14.7. It demonstrates the core concepts (case data modeling, constraint formulation, solver invocation, schedule extraction, and intraday replanning) using Google OR-Tools' CP-SAT solver. It is not production-ready. The case list is small, durations are deterministic, and there's no EHR integration or real-time event stream. Think of it as the whiteboard sketch that helps you understand how the optimization model actually works. A starting point, not a destination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m >
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > The main recipe uses ECS Fargate for solver hosting and EventBridge for real-time surgical events. This example runs everything locally with OR-Tools and writes results to DynamoDB. The optimization math is identical; the infrastructure is stripped away so you can focus on the model.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the constraint programming solver and AWS SDK installed:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 ortools
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m `ortools` is Google's open-source optimization suite. The CP-SAT solver inside it is excellent for scheduling problems because it natively understands interval variables, no-overlap constraints, and optional tasks. It's free, actively maintained, and fast enough for hospital-scale problems (50-80 cases across 15-20 rooms) without a commercial license.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs AWS credentials configured (via environment variables, instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:PutItem`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:GetItem`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:Query`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m For the full pipeline (with ECS hosting, EventBridge routing, and SQS buffering), you'd also need `ecs:RunTask`, `events:PutEvents`, and `sqs:SendMessage`, but this example keeps the focus on the optimization itself.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Configuration and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import datetime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import timezone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from typing import Optional
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from ortools.sat.python import cp_model
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 3, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Table where we store optimized schedules.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SCHEDULE_TABLE_NAME = "or-schedules"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Block time boundaries. Most ORs run 7:00 AM to 5:00 PM (600 minutes).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # We model time in minutes from block start for cleaner arithmetic.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BLOCK_START_HOUR = 7
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BLOCK_END_HOUR = 17
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BLOCK_DURATION_MINUTES = (BLOCK_END_HOUR - BLOCK_START_HOUR) * 60  # 600
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Turnover time between cases (minutes). This is the time to clean the room,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # set up for the next case, and bring the patient in. Varies by case type.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m TURNOVER_TIMES = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "clean_to_clean": 25,       # standard case followed by standard case
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "clean_to_contaminated": 30, # need extra prep for contaminated case
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "contaminated_to_clean": 40, # terminal clean required
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "contaminated_to_contaminated": 35,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Default turnover if we can't classify the transition.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m DEFAULT_TURNOVER_MINUTES = 30
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Shared equipment setup time (minutes). When two cases need the same
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # equipment (e.g., da Vinci robot), there's additional setup between them.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m EQUIPMENT_SETUP_MINUTES = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "robot_davinci": 30,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "c_arm": 15,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "microscope": 20,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "laser": 15,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Penalty weights for the objective function.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # The solver minimizes the weighted sum of these penalties.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PENALTY_WEIGHTS = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "overtime_per_minute": 10,       # each minute past block end costs this much
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "idle_gap_per_minute": 1,        # each minute of idle time between cases
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "preference_violation": 50,      # violating a surgeon's "first case" preference
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "late_start_per_minute": 2,      # each minute a case starts after its ideal window
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Solver time limits.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BATCH_SOLVE_SECONDS = 300    # 5 minutes for overnight planning
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m REPLAN_SOLVE_SECONDS = 30    # 30 seconds for intraday replanning
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Replan threshold: only trigger re-optimization if a case deviates
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # by more than this many minutes from its scheduled end time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m REPLAN_THRESHOLD_MINUTES = 15
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Sample Data: Today's Surgical Cases
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m In production, this comes from the EHR surgical scheduling system via HL7/FHIR integration, enriched with duration predictions from a historical model. Here we hardcode a realistic example so you can see the data structures the solver expects.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
