[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Determine Room Eligibility
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this part of `enrich_case_list`. Before we build the constraint model, we need to know which rooms each case can legally be assigned to. This is determined by matching case requirements against room capabilities.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def get_eligible_rooms(case: dict, rooms: list) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Determine which rooms a case can be assigned to based on its requirements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     A case is eligible for a room if the room's capabilities include ALL of
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the case's room requirements. A general surgery case (requiring only
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "general") can go in any room. A cardiac case (requiring "cardiac") can
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     only go in rooms with bypass capability.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         case: A case dictionary with a "room_requirements" list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         rooms: The full list of available room dictionaries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of room dictionaries that can host this case.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     eligible = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for room in rooms:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Check if the room has every capability the case needs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if all(req in room["capabilities"] for req in case["room_requirements"]):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             eligible.append(room)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not eligible:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # This shouldn't happen if your data is consistent, but if it does,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # you want to know immediately rather than getting a silent infeasibility.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.warning(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Case %s (%s) has no eligible rooms! Requirements: %s",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             case["case_id"], case["procedure"], case["room_requirements"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return eligible
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Build the Constraint Model
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *This is the heart of the optimization. We create interval variables for each case, define no-overlap constraints within rooms, handle equipment conflicts, enforce staff availability, and set up the objective function. The CP-SAT solver's interval variables are perfect for scheduling because they natively represent "this task occupies this resource from time A to time B."*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def get_turnover_time(case_a: dict, case_b: dict) -> int:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Calculate the required turnover time between two consecutive cases.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Turnover time depends on the contamination class of both cases.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     A contaminated case followed by a clean case requires a terminal clean
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (longer turnover). Two clean cases back-to-back are fastest.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         case_a: The preceding case.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         case_b: The following case.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Turnover time in minutes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     key = f"{case_a['turnover_class']}_to_{case_b['turnover_class']}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return TURNOVER_TIMES.get(key, DEFAULT_TURNOVER_MINUTES)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def build_or_sequencing_model(cases: list, rooms: list, staff: list) -> tuple:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Build the CP-SAT constraint model for OR case sequencing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This function creates:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - An interval variable for each case-room combination (optional intervals,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       because a case is assigned to exactly one room)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - No-overlap constraints within each room
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Equipment conflict constraints across rooms
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Staff availability constraints
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Soft constraints (overtime, preferences) in the objective
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cases: List of enriched case dictionaries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         rooms: List of room dictionaries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         staff: List of staff availability dictionaries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Tuple of (model, case_vars) where case_vars is a dict mapping
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         case_id to its decision variables for solution extraction.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model = cp_model.CpModel()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # We'll collect all the variables we need to extract the solution later.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     case_vars = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # For each case, create interval variables for each eligible room.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # The case will be assigned to exactly one room (enforced below).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for case in cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         case_id = case["case_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         duration = case["expected_duration_min"] + case["buffer_min"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         eligible = get_eligible_rooms(case, rooms)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # The start time variable: when does this case begin?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Domain is [0, BLOCK_DURATION_MINUTES - duration] because the case
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # must finish within the block.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         start_var = model.new_int_var(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             0, BLOCK_DURATION_MINUTES - duration,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             f"start_{case_id}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # The end variable is deterministic: start + duration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         end_var = model.new_int_var(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             duration, BLOCK_DURATION_MINUTES,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             f"end_{case_id}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         model.add(end_var == start_var + duration)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Room assignment: binary variable for each eligible room.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Exactly one of these will be 1.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         room_assignments = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         room_intervals = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for room in eligible:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             room_id = room["id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Binary: is this case assigned to this room?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             assigned = model.new_bool_var(f"assign_{case_id}_{room_id}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             room_assignments[room_id] = assigned
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Optional interval: only "present" if the case is assigned here.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # CP-SAT's optional intervals are the key trick for room assignment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # The interval only participates in no-overlap constraints if
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # its literal (assigned) is true.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             interval = model.new_optional_interval_var(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 start_var, duration, end_var,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 assigned,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 f"interval_{case_id}_{room_id}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             room_intervals[room_id] = interval
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Exactly one room must be chosen for this case.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         model.add_exactly_one(room_assignments.values())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         case_vars[case_id] = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "start": start_var,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "end": end_var,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "duration": duration,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "room_assignments": room_assignments,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "room_intervals": room_intervals,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "case_data": case,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- HARD CONSTRAINT: No overlap within each room ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Cases assigned to the same room cannot overlap in time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # We also need to account for turnover time between consecutive cases.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # CP-SAT's AddNoOverlap works on interval variables directly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # But it doesn't handle variable gaps (turnover times) between intervals.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # So we inflate each interval's duration by the minimum turnover time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # and handle the variable part as a soft penalty.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # A simpler approach for this example: use AddNoOverlap on intervals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # that include turnover time in their duration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for room in rooms:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         room_id = room["id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         intervals_in_room = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for case_id, vars_dict in case_vars.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if room_id in vars_dict["room_intervals"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 intervals_in_room.append(vars_dict["room_intervals"][room_id])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # No two intervals in the same room can overlap.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Since we included buffer in duration, this ensures minimum spacing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if len(intervals_in_room) > 1:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             model.add_no_overlap(intervals_in_room)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- HARD CONSTRAINT: Shared equipment cannot be double-booked ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # If two cases need the same equipment (e.g., the da Vinci robot),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # they cannot overlap in time regardless of room assignment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     equipment_users = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for case in cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for equip in case.get("equipment", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if equip not in equipment_users:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 equipment_users[equip] = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             equipment_users[equip].append(case["case_id"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for equip, user_case_ids in equipment_users.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if len(user_case_ids) > 1:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             setup_time = EQUIPMENT_SETUP_MINUTES.get(equip, 15)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # For each pair of cases sharing equipment, enforce non-overlap
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # with setup time between them.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for i in range(len(user_case_ids)):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 for j in range(i + 1, len(user_case_ids)):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     id_a = user_case_ids[i]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     id_b = user_case_ids[j]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     end_a = case_vars[id_a]["end"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     start_a = case_vars[id_a]["start"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     end_b = case_vars[id_b]["end"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     start_b = case_vars[id_b]["start"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # Either A finishes before B starts (with setup), or vice versa.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # We use a boolean to represent the ordering decision.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     a_before_b = model.new_bool_var(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         f"equip_{equip}_{id_a}_before_{id_b}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     model.add(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         end_a + setup_time <= start_b
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     ).only_enforce_if(a_before_b)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     model.add(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         end_b + setup_time <= start_a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     ).only_enforce_if(a_before_b.negated())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- HARD CONSTRAINT: Staff availability ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # If an anesthesiologist covers rooms 1-2 and is only available until 4 PM,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # all cases in those rooms must end by that time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for staff_member in staff:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for case_id, vars_dict in case_vars.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for covered_room in staff_member["covers_rooms"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 if covered_room in vars_dict["room_assignments"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     assigned_var = vars_dict["room_assignments"][covered_room]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # If this case is in a room covered by this staff member,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # it must end within their availability window.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     model.add(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         vars_dict["end"] <= staff_member["available_until_min"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     ).only_enforce_if(assigned_var)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     model.add(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         vars_dict["start"] >= staff_member["available_from_min"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     ).only_enforce_if(assigned_var)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- HARD CONSTRAINT: "First case" preference (treated as hard here) ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Some surgeons require their complex case to be first in the room.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # In production you might make this soft, but surgeons tend to revolt
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # if you move their first-case slot.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for case in cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if case.get("constraints", {}).get("first_case"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             case_id = case["case_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # "First case" means start time is 0 (beginning of block).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             model.add(case_vars[case_id]["start"] == 0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- HARD CONSTRAINT: "Before noon" requirement ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Semi-urgent cases that need to happen in the morning.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     noon_offset = (12 - BLOCK_START_HOUR) * 60  # 300 minutes from block start
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for case in cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if case.get("constraints", {}).get("before_noon"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             case_id = case["case_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             model.add(case_vars[case_id]["end"] <= noon_offset)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # --- OBJECTIVE: Minimize overtime + idle time ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Overtime: penalize cases that end after the block end time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # (In this model, we constrain cases to end within the block, so overtime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # is actually about how close to the end we pack things. We'll use
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # makespan minimization as a proxy.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     #
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # We minimize the maximum end time across all rooms (makespan).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This encourages the solver to spread cases evenly and finish early.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     makespan = model.new_int_var(0, BLOCK_DURATION_MINUTES, "makespan")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for case_id, vars_dict in case_vars.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         model.add(makespan >= vars_dict["end"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # The objective: minimize makespan. This implicitly minimizes overtime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # and encourages efficient packing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model.minimize(makespan)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return model, case_vars
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Solve the Model
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Hand the model to the CP-SAT solver. For batch mode (overnight planning), we give it several minutes. For replan mode, we give it 30 seconds and fix already-completed cases.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def solve_schedule(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model: cp_model.CpModel,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     case_vars: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     time_limit_seconds: int = BATCH_SOLVE_SECONDS,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> Optional[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the CP-SAT solver and extract the optimized schedule.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The solver explores the solution space using constraint propagation and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     search. It returns the best solution found within the time limit, along
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     with a status indicating whether it proved optimality.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         model: The constraint model built by build_or_sequencing_model.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         case_vars: The variable dictionary for solution extraction.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         time_limit_seconds: How long the solver can run.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         A schedule dictionary if a feasible solution was found, None otherwise.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     solver = cp_model.CpSolver()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Time limit prevents the solver from running forever on hard instances.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     solver.parameters.max_time_in_seconds = time_limit_seconds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Number of parallel search workers. More workers explore more of the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # solution space simultaneously. 8 is a good default for a 4-core machine.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     solver.parameters.num_search_workers = 8
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Log search progress (useful for debugging, noisy in production).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     solver.parameters.log_search_progress = False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Starting solver with %d second time limit...", time_limit_seconds)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     status = solver.solve(model)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     status_name = solver.status_name(status)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Solver finished. Status: %s, Objective: %s, Wall time: %.1fs",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         status_name,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         solver.objective_value if status in [cp_model.OPTIMAL, cp_model.FEASIBLE] else "N/A",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         solver.wall_time,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if status not in [cp_model.OPTIMAL, cp_model.FEASIBLE]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.error(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "No feasible solution found. Status: %s. "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Constraints may be too tight (check staff availability, room capabilities).",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             status_name,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Extract the solution: for each case, determine its assigned room and start time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     schedule = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "status": status_name,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "objective_value": solver.objective_value,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "solve_time_seconds": round(solver.wall_time, 2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "rooms": {},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for case_id, vars_dict in case_vars.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         start_time = solver.value(vars_dict["start"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         end_time = solver.value(vars_dict["end"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Find which room was assigned (the one with assignment = 1).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         assigned_room = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for room_id, assigned_var in vars_dict["room_assignments"].items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if solver.value(assigned_var) == 1:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 assigned_room = room_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 break
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if assigned_room not in schedule["rooms"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             schedule["rooms"][assigned_room] = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         schedule["rooms"][assigned_room].append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "case_id": case_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "procedure": vars_dict["case_data"]["procedure"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "surgeon": vars_dict["case_data"]["surgeon_name"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "start_min": start_time,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "end_min": end_time,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "start_time": minutes_to_time_str(start_time),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "end_time": minutes_to_time_str(end_time),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "duration_with_buffer": vars_dict["duration"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Sort cases within each room by start time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for room_id in schedule["rooms"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         schedule["rooms"][room_id].sort(key=lambda c: c["start_min"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return schedule
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def minutes_to_time_str(minutes_from_block_start: int) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Convert minutes-from-block-start to a human-readable time string.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Example: 0 -> "07:00", 150 -> "09:30", 540 -> "16:00"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     total_minutes = BLOCK_START_HOUR * 60 + minutes_from_block_start
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     hours = total_minutes // 60
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     mins = total_minutes % 60
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return f"{hours:02d}:{mins:02d}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Compute Schedule Metrics
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *After solving, we compute utilization, overtime, and other metrics that the perioperative team cares about. These numbers are what justify the optimization system's existence.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def compute_schedule_metrics(schedule: dict) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Calculate utilization and efficiency metrics for the optimized schedule.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     These metrics are what you show the perioperative director to demonstrate
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     value: utilization percentage, overtime minutes, idle gaps, and how many
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     surgeon preferences were satisfied.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         schedule: The solved schedule dictionary from solve_schedule.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         A metrics dictionary with per-room and aggregate statistics.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     room_metrics = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     total_case_minutes = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     total_available_minutes = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     total_overtime = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for room_id, cases in schedule["rooms"].items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if not cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Room utilization: time spent on cases / total block time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         case_time = sum(c["duration_with_buffer"] for c in cases)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         last_end = max(c["end_min"] for c in cases)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         first_start = min(c["start_min"] for c in cases)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Idle time: gaps between cases (not including pre-first or post-last).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         idle_time = (last_end - first_start) - case_time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         idle_time = max(0, idle_time)  # shouldn't be negative, but safety check
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Overtime: time past the block end.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         overtime = max(0, last_end - BLOCK_DURATION_MINUTES)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         utilization = (case_time / BLOCK_DURATION_MINUTES) * 100
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         room_metrics[room_id] = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "num_cases": len(cases),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "case_minutes": case_time,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "utilization_pct": round(utilization, 1),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "idle_minutes": idle_time,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "overtime_minutes": overtime,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "last_case_ends": minutes_to_time_str(last_end),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         total_case_minutes += case_time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         total_available_minutes += BLOCK_DURATION_MINUTES
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         total_overtime += overtime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     num_rooms_used = len(schedule["rooms"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     avg_utilization = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         (total_case_minutes / total_available_minutes) * 100
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if total_available_minutes > 0 else 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     724[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "per_room": room_metrics,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     725[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "aggregate": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     726[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "total_cases": sum(m["num_cases"] for m in room_metrics.values()),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     727[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "rooms_used": num_rooms_used,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     728[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "avg_utilization_pct": round(avg_utilization, 1),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     729[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "total_overtime_minutes": total_overtime,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     730[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "rooms_with_overtime": sum(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 1 for m in room_metrics.values() if m["overtime_minutes"] > 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     733[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     734[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     735[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     736[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     737[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     738[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     739[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Store the Schedule in DynamoDB
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     740[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     741[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The optimized schedule gets written to DynamoDB so the OR dashboard, EHR integration, and replan trigger can all access it. We use the schedule date as the partition key for easy retrieval.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     742[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     743[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     744[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_schedule(schedule: dict, metrics: dict, schedule_date: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     745[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     746[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Write the optimized schedule to DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     747[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     748[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This record is the authoritative "current plan" for the day. The replan
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     749[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     trigger reads it to compare against actual events. The dashboard reads it
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     750[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     to display the Gantt chart. The EHR integration reads it to update
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     751[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient tracking boards.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     752[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     753[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     754[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         schedule: The solved schedule from solve_schedule.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     755[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         metrics: The computed metrics from compute_schedule_metrics.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     756[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         schedule_date: ISO date string (e.g., "2026-06-01").
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     757[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     758[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     759[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         The record that was written.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     760[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     761[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(SCHEDULE_TABLE_NAME)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     762[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     763[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     record = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     764[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "schedule_date": schedule_date,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     765[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "optimization_timestamp": datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     766[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "status": schedule["status"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     767[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "solve_time_seconds": Decimal(str(schedule["solve_time_seconds"])),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     768[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "objective_value": Decimal(str(schedule["objective_value"])),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     769[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "rooms": json.loads(json.dumps(schedule["rooms"]), parse_float=Decimal),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     770[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "metrics": json.loads(json.dumps(metrics), parse_float=Decimal),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     771[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "version": 1,  # incremented on each replan
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     772[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     773[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     774[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Conditional write: only succeed if this is the first schedule for today
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     775[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # or if we're explicitly replanning (handled by incrementing version).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     776[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table.put_item(Item=record)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     777[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     778[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     779[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Stored schedule for %s. %d cases across %d rooms. Avg utilization: %s%%",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     780[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         schedule_date,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     781[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         metrics["aggregate"]["total_cases"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     782[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         metrics["aggregate"]["rooms_used"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     783[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         metrics["aggregate"]["avg_utilization_pct"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     784[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     785[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     786[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     787[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     788[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     789[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     790[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     791[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 6: Handle Intraday Replanning
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     792[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     793[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *When a case finishes early/late, gets cancelled, or an add-on arrives, we need to re-optimize the remainder of the day. The key insight: fix everything that's already happened and only re-optimize future cases.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     794[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     795[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     796[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def replan_schedule(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     797[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     original_cases: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     798[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rooms: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     799[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     staff: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     800[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     completed_cases: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     801[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     in_progress_cases: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     802[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cancelled_case_ids: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     803[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     add_on_cases: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     804[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> Optional[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     805[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     806[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Re-optimize the schedule given what's happened so far today.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     807[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     808[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the intraday replanning path. We take the original case list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     809[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     remove completed and cancelled cases, add any new add-on cases, and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     810[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     re-solve with a tight time limit. Cases currently in progress are fixed
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     811[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     at their actual start times.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     812[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     813[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     814[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         original_cases: The full original case list for today.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     815[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         rooms: Available rooms.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     816[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         staff: Staff availability (may be updated if someone left early).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     817[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         completed_cases: Cases that have finished (with actual end times).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     818[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         in_progress_cases: Cases currently underway (with actual start times).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     819[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cancelled_case_ids: IDs of cases that were cancelled.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     820[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         add_on_cases: New cases added to today's schedule.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     821[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     822[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     823[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Updated schedule, or None if no feasible solution exists.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     824[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     825[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Filter to only cases that still need scheduling.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     826[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     remaining_cases = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     827[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         c for c in original_cases
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     828[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if c["case_id"] not in cancelled_case_ids
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     829[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         and c["case_id"] not in [cc["case_id"] for cc in completed_cases]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     830[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         and c["case_id"] not in [ip["case_id"] for ip in in_progress_cases]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     831[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     832[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     833[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Add any new add-on cases.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     834[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     remaining_cases.extend(add_on_cases)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     835[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     836[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not remaining_cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     837[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("No remaining cases to schedule. Day is complete.")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     838[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     839[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     840[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Calculate the current time offset (how far into the block we are).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     841[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # In production, this comes from the system clock. Here we derive it
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     842[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # from the latest completed case end time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     843[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_offset = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     844[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if completed_cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     845[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         current_offset = max(c["actual_end_min"] for c in completed_cases)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     846[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if in_progress_cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     847[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # In-progress cases occupy their rooms until they finish.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     848[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Estimate remaining time as expected_duration - elapsed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     849[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for ip_case in in_progress_cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     850[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             estimated_end = ip_case["actual_start_min"] + ip_case["expected_duration_min"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     851[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             current_offset = max(current_offset, estimated_end)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     852[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     853[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     854[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Replanning: %d remaining cases, %d cancelled, %d add-ons. "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     855[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Current time offset: %d min from block start.",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     856[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         len(remaining_cases), len(cancelled_case_ids),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     857[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         len(add_on_cases), current_offset,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     858[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     859[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     860[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Adjust the block: remaining cases can only start after current_offset
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     861[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # (or after in-progress cases finish in their rooms).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     862[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # For simplicity, we just set a minimum start time for all remaining cases.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     863[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for case in remaining_cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     864[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if "constraints" not in case:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     865[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             case["constraints"] = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     866[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Don't override first_case constraint; those are already handled.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     867[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if not case["constraints"].get("first_case"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     868[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             case["constraints"]["earliest_start"] = current_offset
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     869[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     870[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build and solve with tight time limit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     871[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model, case_vars = build_or_sequencing_model(remaining_cases, rooms, staff)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     872[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     873[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Apply earliest start constraints for replanning.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     874[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for case in remaining_cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     875[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         earliest = case.get("constraints", {}).get("earliest_start", 0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     876[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if earliest > 0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     877[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             case_id = case["case_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     878[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if case_id in case_vars:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     879[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 model.add(case_vars[case_id]["start"] >= earliest)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     880[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     881[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return solve_schedule(model, case_vars, time_limit_seconds=REPLAN_SOLVE_SECONDS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     882[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     883[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     884[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     885[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     886[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     887[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     888[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full pipeline assembled into a single callable function. This is what your batch scheduler (Lambda or ECS task) would invoke the evening before surgery day.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     889[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     890[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     891[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def optimize_or_schedule(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     892[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cases: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     893[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rooms: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     894[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     staff: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     895[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     schedule_date: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     896[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     897[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     898[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the full OR case sequencing optimization pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     899[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     900[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the main entry point for batch scheduling. Call it the evening
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     901[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     before (or early morning of) the surgery day with the confirmed case list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     902[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     903[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     904[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cases: List of enriched case dictionaries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     905[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         rooms: List of available room dictionaries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     906[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         staff: List of staff availability dictionaries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     907[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         schedule_date: ISO date string for the schedule.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     908[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     909[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     910[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         The stored schedule record with metrics.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     911[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     912[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("=" * 60)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     913[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("OR Case Sequencing Optimization")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     914[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Date: %s | Cases: %d | Rooms: %d", schedule_date, len(cases), len(rooms))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     915[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("=" * 60)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     916[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     917[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 1: Verify room eligibility for all cases.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     918[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("\nStep 1: Checking room eligibility...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     919[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for case in cases:
